<p>I have a simple table. Then I tried to add unique key in my table</p>  <pre><code>ALTER TABLE BARANG  ADD CONSTRAINT uc_coba UNIQUE (barang_nama,nama_supplier) </code></pre>  <p>Then I want to use <code>uc_coba</code> as foreign key on other table</p>  <pre><code> ALTER TABLE jual   ADD CONSTRAINT uc_cek FOREIGN KEY (barang_nama,nama_supplier)  REFERENCES barang(barang_nama,nama_supplier) ON UPDATE CASCADE ON DELETE CASCADE </code></pre>  <p>But it shows error message like this</p>  <blockquote>   <p>Msg 1785, Level 16, State 0, Line 1</p>      <p>Introducing FOREIGN KEY constraint 'uc_pink' on table 'jual' may cause   cycles or multiple cascade paths. Specify ON DELETE NO ACTION or ON   UPDATE NO ACTION, or modify other FOREIGN KEY constraints.</p> </blockquote>  <p>Then I remove <code>ON UPDATE CASCADE ON DELETE CASCADE</code> from my sql syntax. And its working.</p>  <p>My question is how to create unique foreign key with ON UPDATE CASCADE ON DELETE CASCADE.</p>